Overview:
  encapsulates each request as an object
  object oriented callback
  decouple sender from the processor
  allows for undo functionality
  object per command
  class contains the 'what'
  very few draw backs
  second most used

examples:
  java lang runnable
  swing action

design:
  object per command
  command interface
  execute method
  undo method
  reflection
  command invoker concrete command

Pitfalls:
  dependence on other command
  multiple commands
  make use of memento
  Prototype for copies